"@SeraphimDawn":/dis/the-time-wasting-thread/post/53d49efb636872418ba00000#post_53d49efb636872418ba00000
It's a modern coyote skull that is dyed to look old, and then set into matrix that sometimes has fossil shells in it. They are sold as Bonner Springs fossils (a real fossil locality in Kansas, but the skulls there are never found with the jaws), and sometimes even have maggot cases, hair and cut marks on them (from trapper's knives).
